President Biden has declared a major disaster for the Navajo Nation and authorized federal aid to assist with recovery efforts from severe winter storms and flooding that occurred in January 2023. The Navajo Nation and certain private nonprofit organizations can receive federal funding for emergency work, facility repairs, and hazard mitigation measures. Benigno B. Ruiz from FEMA has been appointed to coordinate federal recovery operations. Further designations may be made based on damage assessments. For more information, the media can contact the FEMA news desk.